article.headline: McCreary scores 30 points and grabs 12 rebounds as Mercer beats Queens 84-65

images.name: Jalyn Mccreary elevates for the big-time block
images.caption: Jalyn Mccreary elevates for the big-time block

article.linkText: McCreary scores 30 points and grabs 12 rebounds as Mercer beats Queens 84-65
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- — Jalyn McCreary's 30 points and 12 rebounds led Mercer over Queens 84-65 on Tuesday night. McCreary also contributed three steals and three blocks for the Bears (5-6). Jalen Cobb added 14 points while shooting 5 for 9, including 4 for 6 from beyond the arc, and he also had 10 rebounds and five assists. Jake Davis shot 5 for 8, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. The Royals (6-7) were led in scoring by Deyton Albury, who finished with 17 points and two steals. AJ McKee added 16 points and two steals for Queens. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
